<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1908-05-09T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1908-05-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Wilson</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1908-05-09"><hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                1908</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>Mr. Wilson’s action, reported his 329, meets with approval this
                            Government, both as to memorandum presented to minister for foreign
                            affairs and reply regarding treatment our communications as unofficial
                            prior to decisive vote upon annexation and to become official
                            immediately thereafter.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Root.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>